  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 05:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] OBI is the Only Indicator That Matters \u2014 V5 Conviction Rewrite\n\n**Task:** Analyze per-indicator performance to find which indicators actually predict wins, and optimize entry parameters.\n\n**Data:** 140 matched trades (signal \u2192 outcome) from March, including all V4.1 era trades.\n\n**Finding 1 \u2014 OBI is the DOMINANT indicator:**\n| Condition | WR | n | Delta |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| OBI\u2705 (all hours) | 65% | 74 | +13pp vs OBI\u274c |\n| OBI\u274c (all hours) | 52% | 66 | coin flip |\n| OBI\u2705 + V4.1 hours | **88%** | 24 | +36pp vs OBI\u274c |\n| OBI\u274c + V4.1 hours | **52%** | 23 | breakeven |\n\nOBI alone accounts for almost ALL of the edge in V4.1 hours. When OBI confirms order flow aligns with our contrarian YES, we win 88% of the time. When it doesn't, we're flipping coins.\n\n**Finding 2 \u2014 MACD is an INVERSE indicator:**\n| MACD | WR | n |\n|---|---|---|\n| MACD \u274c (opposed) | **87%** | 15 |\n| MACD \u2705 (aligned) | 55% | 125 |\n\nMACD opposing our trade = we're buying a REVERSAL (momentum against us, but market turns). This makes perfect sense for a contrarian strategy: we WANT to enter when momentum indicators say \"wrong way\" because we're fading the move.\n\n**Finding 3 \u2014 CVD adds modest edge, VWAP is noise:**\n- CVD: +13pp when aligned (60% vs 47%)\n- VWAP: -3pp when aligned (58% vs 61%) \u2014 literally noise\n- Current system treats all 4 equally at 1 conviction point each. Wrong.\n\n**Finding 4 \u2014 Cross-tab reveals the golden combo:**\n- OBI\u2705 + MACD\u274c (V4.1 hours): **100% WR** (6W/0L)\n- OBI\u2705 + MACD\u2705 (V4.1 hours): 82% WR (14W/3L)  \n- OBI\u274c + MACD\u2705 (V4.1 hours): 50% WR (11W/11L) \u2014 ZERO edge\n- Conv 4/4: 67% WR (18 trades) vs Conv 3/4: 58% WR (120 trades)\n\n**My thinking:** The conviction system needs a total rewrite for V5. Currently we count 3/4 indicators aligned = trade, 4/4 = reduce. This is wrong because:\n1. OBI is worth ~3x any other indicator (+36pp edge)\n2. MACD should be INVERTED for contrarian YES (opposed MACD = good)\n3. VWAP adds zero edge\n4. CVD is modestly useful but secondary to OBI\n\n**V5 Conviction Proposal (weighted):**\n- OBI\u2705 = +3 points (mandatory for high conviction)\n- CVD\u2705 = +1 point\n- MACD\u274c = +1 point (INVERTED \u2014 opposed MACD is bullish for contrarian)\n- VWAP = 0 points (removed from scoring)\n- Threshold: 3+ points to trade (OBI alone = 3, enough with nothing else)\n- Max: 5 points (OBI\u2705 + CVD\u2705 + MACD\u274c) \u2192 full Kelly size\n\n**Deployment plan:**\n1. V5a (this week): min_bias=45 only (safe, data-backed)\n2. V5b (next week): OBI weighting + MACD inversion (needs more OBI\u2705 data)\n3. V5c: liquidation detector integration\n\n**Risk:** OBI\u2705 + V4.1 = 24 trades. Need 50+ for statistical confidence. Collecting more this week under V4.1 before rewriting conviction.\n\n**Next P2:** After V5a deployment, track OBI\u2705/\u274c split on every trade for one week to build the 50-trade dataset needed to greenlight V5b.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 04:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Copy Intel Pipeline is Fee",
